programme.desc: Who is the bloody figure wielding a meat cleaver, seen racing through the alleys of British Columbia’s Chinatown? Whoever he is, he has terrified dozens of witnesses, who have never been the same afterwards. The brutal history of Cornwall Jail, Ottawa’s most notorious prison, lives on as ghostly apparitions of tortured inmates terrorize modern visitors. In its heyday it was home to vicious criminals, and sadistic guards. Hangings, whippings and torture were daily affairs and spirits from that era still linger on in the maze of cell blocks and corridors. Many male criminals were hanged at the Northwest Mounted Police outpost known as Fort Saskatchewan, but only one woman. Florence Lassandro was dubbed the Mob Princess, and her spirit is one of many seen on the grounds and in the preserved buildings of this historic site. Journey through several of the world's most haunted prisons and experience real portals to hell on earth.

programme.title: Largest Public Land Ram in Utah 194"
programme.desc: We were very fortunate to play a roll in capturing Kyle Ekker's hunt on film. Kyle Ekker grew up in Green River Utah where he developed his love of hunting, chasing mulies on the Book Cliffs. He has worked for the Emery County Sheriff's Office for 30 years where he is currently employed as a captain. He has been a member of the Utah FNAWS for the last 10 years and through this he is able to share his passion for the outdoors & wild sheep. In December of 2015 he drew the highly coveted Rocky Mountain Bighorn Sportsman's permit. This tag gave him the opportunity to hunt sheep from the beginning of September to December 31st on almost any open units in the state. He hunted every opportunity that he had he could in pursuit of his dream ram. On November 30th things came together for him and he was able to harvest a very magnificent ram. With an unofficial green score of 194" this ram will be the largest public land ram ever killed in the state of Utah.

However, before the team can deploy, escalating terrorist activity dramatically raises the threat level. Facing a surge of hostile forces, the All-Stars must come together to secure their principal and ensure their safety at all costs. When they're caught on the X with no clear way out, there's only one option left—eliminate the threat. Who will survive the mission? And who will emerge victorious?

programme.title: Wild Shots
programme.desc: Tim heads to the Smoky Mountains for an action-packed adventure that’s as sharp as it gets. The journey kicks off at the world-famous Smoky Mountain Knife Works, the largest knife store on the planet, where Tim explores the artistry and precision behind the blades of We Knife. There, he reconnects with shooting legend Kyle Lamb, who shares his thoughts on the craftsmanship that keeps professionals equipped for anything. The action continues at Buds Gun Shop, where Tim joins Kyle once again to complete two of Lamb’s signature courses—the intense “Chaos Drill” and the dynamic “Triple Threat.” Together, they test speed, accuracy, and the mental discipline needed to master the range. But the day wouldn’t be complete without a little backwoods ingenuity. IraqVeteran8888 joins Tim for a bit of unconventional fun—combining creativity, curiosity, and some good old Redneck Science to wrap up an unforgettable episode.

programme.title: Surviving Mann
programme.desc: The day kicks off with a one-of-a-kind “hatting ceremony” as Don Mann is crowned—then quite literally set on fire. But there’s no time to admire the flames; Ken Shamrock is waiting with another round of punishing Lion’s Den training. With Iron Man training just one day away, the pressure is at an all-time high. Contestant Landon reflects on his past Surviving Mann experience, paying tribute to the mentors who guided him—and now stepping into that role himself. The countdown to mission time begins as gear is packed, coordinates plotted, and details roll in via Red Cat Drones. With the ISR team deployed, the first phase of the mission is underway. Every contestant must be ready to deliver their cover for status in an instant—because in this game, hesitation can be the difference between success and failure.

programme.title: Surviving Mann
programme.desc: The path to mission readiness takes a sharp turn as contestants are introduced to the Cupolster—an innovative holster system that changes the game when seconds matter. Don delivers a critical safety lesson before the team puts the gear to the test, running a demanding course of fire from inside a truck. From standard draws to Cupolster drills, every move is about speed, precision, and survival under pressure. The action escalates with a SAR9 passenger-seat course of fire that leaves contestants breathless —proving that combat can come from anywhere, at any time. But the real trial begins when Ken Shamrock unleashes his legendary Iron Man challenge. In three-minute elimination rounds, contestants go toe-to-toe against each other, testing not only strength but everything they’ve absorbed under Shamrock’s punishing guidance. It’s survival of the fittest—where only the toughest, sharpest, and most disciplined will walk away victorious.

programme.title: Farm Hero
programme.desc: In part one of the season finale, Laura is immersing herself in all the wonders that are TomKat ranch. Created by Kat Taylor and Tom Steyer, TomKat ranch is part ranch, part laboratory, part educational facility and all around the American Dream. This ranch is doing their part at spear-heading the rural revitalization that will bring about climate stability and a healthier planet.

programme.title: Operation Bank Robbery: Breaking The Bank
programme.desc: Ken Dye goes undercover for the St. Louis County Sheriff's Department to purchase illegal weapons and hears about a planned bank heist. He is hired to help the would-be bank robbers stick up a local bank. But Dye discovers that the mastermind plans to enact vengeance for being refused a loan, and kill the bank president. Dye plays along to gather evidence against the criminals and arrest them before they go rogue and pull the job without him.

programme.title: Operation Canned Tomatoes: Italian Mafia
programme.desc: FBI agent Ron Moretti enters the dangerous world of the Italian mafia, while investigating the supply of heroin into the US. Moretti devises a plan to have the mafia ship their white powder inside canned tomatoes, but the FDA blocks the plan because of their culinary concerns. During the two-year long operation, Moretti becomes the shipping point of Italian heroin, while dodging international governments before taking the traffickers down.

programme.title: Operation Cockfight: Underworld Gambling
programme.desc: Stan Sales of the Honolulu PD enters the world of cockfighting, a popular entertainment on the island. Sales and his partners go undercover to videotape and document a local promotor who controls the cockfights and takes a piece of all the action. They eventually arrest the promoter and shut down his illegal operation for good.

programme.title: Operation Bank Robbery: Breaking The Bank
programme.desc: Ken Dye goes undercover for the St. Louis County Sheriff's Department to purchase illegal weapons and hears about a planned bank heist. He is hired to help the would-be bank robbers stick up a local bank. But Dye discovers that the mastermind plans to enact vengeance for being refused a loan, and kill the bank president. Dye plays along to gather evidence against the criminals and arrest them before they go rogue and pull the job without him.

programme.title: Operation Canned Tomatoes: Italian Mafia
programme.desc: FBI agent Ron Moretti enters the dangerous world of the Italian mafia, while investigating the supply of heroin into the US. Moretti devises a plan to have the mafia ship their white powder inside canned tomatoes, but the FDA blocks the plan because of their culinary concerns. During the two-year long operation, Moretti becomes the shipping point of Italian heroin, while dodging international governments before taking the traffickers down.

During the two-year long operation, Moretti becomes the shipping point of Italian heroin, while dodging international governments before taking the traffickers down.

programme.title: Operation Cockfight: Underworld Gambling
programme.desc: Stan Sales of the Honolulu PD enters the world of cockfighting, a popular entertainment on the island. Sales and his partners go undercover to videotape and document a local promotor who controls the cockfights and takes a piece of all the action. They eventually arrest the promoter and shut down his illegal operation for good.

programme.title: Operation Bank Robbery: Breaking The Bank
programme.desc: Ken Dye goes undercover for the St. Louis County Sheriff's Department to purchase illegal weapons and hears about a planned bank heist. He is hired to help the would-be bank robbers stick up a local bank. But Dye discovers that the mastermind plans to enact vengeance for being refused a loan, and kill the bank president. Dye plays along to gather evidence against the criminals and arrest them before they go rogue and pull the job without him.

programme.title: Operation Canned Tomatoes: Italian Mafia
programme.desc: FBI agent Ron Moretti enters the dangerous world of the Italian mafia, while investigating the supply of heroin into the US. Moretti devises a plan to have the mafia ship their white powder inside canned tomatoes, but the FDA blocks the plan because of their culinary concerns. During the two-year long operation, Moretti becomes the shipping point of Italian heroin, while dodging international governments before taking the traffickers down.

programme.title: Operation Cockfight: Underworld Gambling
programme.desc: Stan Sales of the Honolulu PD enters the world of cockfighting, a popular entertainment on the island. Sales and his partners go undercover to videotape and document a local promotor who controls the cockfights and takes a piece of all the action. They eventually arrest the promoter and shut down his illegal operation for good.

programme.title: Operation Bank Robbery: Breaking The Bank
programme.desc: Ken Dye goes undercover for the St. Louis County Sheriff's Department to purchase illegal weapons and hears about a planned bank heist. He is hired to help the would-be bank robbers stick up a local bank. But Dye discovers that the mastermind plans to enact vengeance for being refused a loan, and kill the bank president. Dye plays along to gather evidence against the criminals and arrest them before they go rogue and pull the job without him.

programme.title: Operation Canned Tomatoes: Italian Mafia
programme.desc: FBI agent Ron Moretti enters the dangerous world of the Italian mafia, while investigating the supply of heroin into the US. Moretti devises a plan to have the mafia ship their white powder inside canned tomatoes, but the FDA blocks the plan because of their culinary concerns. During the two-year long operation, Moretti becomes the shipping point of Italian heroin, while dodging international governments before taking the traffickers down.
